{"abstract":[{"text":"This parameter defines the range for the fade-out effect before an automatic content cutoff on pitched map views. Fade out is implemented by scaling down and removing buildings in the fade range in a staggered fashion. Opacity is not changed. The fade range is expressed in relation to the height of the map view. A value of 1.0 indicates that the content is faded to the same extent as the map’s height in pixels, while a value close to zero represents a sharp cutoff. When the value is set to 0.0, the cutoff is completely disabled. Note: The property has no effect on the map if terrain is enabled.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Default value: 0. Value range: [0, 1]","type":"text"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"fillExtrusionCutoffFadeRange","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"_","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"constant","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sd","text":"Double"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"FillExtrusionLayer","preciseIdentifier":"s:10MapboxMaps18FillExtrusionLayerV","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.mapbox.MapboxMaps\/documentation\/MapboxMaps\/FillExtrusionLayer"}]}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/mapboxmaps\/fillextrusionlayer\/fillextrusioncutofffaderange(_:)-2kfwa"]}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"roleHeading":"Instance Method","modules":[{"name":"MapboxMaps"}],"extendedModule":"MapboxMaps","role":"symbol","externalID":"s:10MapboxMaps18FillExtrusionLayerV04fillD15CutoffFadeRangeyACSdF","symbolKind":"method","title":"fillExtrusionCutoffFadeRange(_:)","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"